---
import BaseLayout from '../components/layout/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Editorial Intelligence in practice"
  description="How an editorial operating system emerged from day-to-day work across research, customer stories, thought leadership, product marketing and AI workflows."
>
  <article class="container-site py-20">
    <div class="max-w-2xl">

      <!-- Header -->
      <header class="mb-16">
        <p class="t-label mb-6">In practice</p>
        <h1 class="t-display mb-6">Editorial Intelligence in practice</h1>
        <p class="t-body text-lg leading-relaxed">
          How an editorial operating system emerged from day-to-day work
        </p>
      </header>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Intro -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <div class="prose-section">
          <p>Every framework on this site began with a practical problem.</p>
          <p>Not a theory. Not a startup idea. Not a consulting framework.</p>
          <p>They emerged while working across research, customer stories, thought leadership, product marketing and event content — most extensively in my work at Sage.</p>
          <p>The challenge was not producing more content. It was making better use of everything we were already learning.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Working together -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="t-label mb-8">Working together</h2>
        <div class="prose-section">
          <p>I work with content and marketing teams who are sitting on good research, real customer insight and genuine expertise — but aren't extracting full value from it.</p>
          <p>The work typically involves building the narrative layer that connects those inputs: identifying the through-lines, developing the strategic argument, and creating the frameworks that make the insight reusable across teams, channels and time.</p>
          <p>If that's a problem you're working on, <a href="/about" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] no-underline hover:underline">get in touch</a>.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- From production to systems -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="t-label mb-8">From content production to knowledge systems</h2>
        <div class="prose-section">
          <p>Modern content marketing often treats projects as standalone deliverables.</p>
          <p>Research becomes a report. An event becomes a blog. A customer interview becomes a case study. Then everyone moves on.</p>
          <p>The effort resets with every cycle. The insight from one project rarely informs the next. Nothing compounds.</p>
          <p>Editorial Intelligence asks a different question:</p>
          <p class="font-medium text-[var(--color-ink)]">What if every piece of work became part of a connected knowledge system?</p>
          <p>Not a library of assets. A system where each new signal strengthens existing narratives, each framework makes the next easier to build, and each piece of evidence raises the quality of everything connected to it.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Flow diagram -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <div class="flow-diagram">
          {[
            { label: 'Day-to-day editorial work', desc: 'Research, events, customer interviews, campaigns' },
            { label: 'Repeated problems', desc: 'The same questions arising across different projects' },
            { label: 'Methods', desc: 'Approaches that consistently produced better results' },
            { label: 'Reusable frameworks', desc: 'Methods documented and made transferable' },
            { label: 'Editorial Intelligence OS', desc: 'The system that connects and compounds them' },
            { label: 'Organisational capability', desc: 'When teams use the methods, not just one person' },
          ].map((step, i) => (
            <div class="flow-step">
              <div class="flow-content">
                <span class="flow-label">{step.label}</span>
                <span class="flow-desc">{step.desc}</span>
              </div>
              {i < 5 && <div class="flow-arrow">↓</div>}
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Examples from practice -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="t-label mb-8">Examples from practice</h2>
        <div class="prose-section mb-8">
          <p>These frameworks didn't emerge from theory. Each one began as a practical problem and developed into a reusable method.</p>
          <p>The Winning in Small H2 editorial brief illustrates what this looks like in practice. The shift it documents — from topic-driven content to pressure-driven systems — is Editorial Intelligence applied to a live content programme.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- WiS editorial system callout -->
        <div class="system-callout mb-8">
          <div class="system-callout-header">
            <span class="system-callout-label">Worked example — Winning in Small H2 2026</span>
          </div>
          <div class="system-callout-cols">
            <div class="system-col system-col--from">
              <span class="system-col-head">From</span>
              <p>A topic-driven, campaign-driven approach. Each asset built once and judged on reach.</p>
              <ul class="system-list">
                <li>MTD content</li>
                <li>AI content</li>
                <li>Growth content</li>
                <li>Standalone assets</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="system-col-arrow">→</div>
            <div class="system-col system-col--to">
              <span class="system-col-head">To</span>
              <p>A pressure-driven, system-driven approach. Content organised around where decisions are being made.</p>
              <ul class="system-list">
                <li>Where pressure builds</li>
                <li>Who carries it</li>
                <li>Connected journeys</li>
                <li>Compounding evidence</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="system-callout-note">Through-line: complexity grows faster than visibility.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="examples-grid">
          {[
            {
              origin: 'Hidden Hours research',
              became: 'Research as reusable narrative',
              desc: 'Survey data became a strategic position that accumulated more evidence with every connected piece.',
            },
            {
              origin: 'Event reporting',
              became: 'Event Intelligence',
              desc: 'Conferences became signal-gathering systems rather than one-off content moments.',
            },
            {
              origin: 'Customer interviews',
              became: 'Customer & Market Signals',
              desc: 'Interview transcripts and notes became a structured evidence base, not isolated case studies.',
            },
            {
              origin: 'Customer stories',
              became: 'AI-supported editorial workflows',
              desc: 'Producing consistent, high-quality customer evidence at scale without losing editorial quality.',
            },
            {
              origin: 'AI adoption research',
              became: 'AI Maturity Curve',
              desc: 'Survey data on AI use became a framework for understanding where capacity gets lost and why.',
            },
            {
              origin: 'CFO research — 1,221 finance leaders',
              became: 'Mid-market thought leadership',
              desc: 'Global survey of senior finance leaders became a three-part narrative on the expanding CFO role, AI adoption gaps and wellbeing. The same structural patterns as Hidden Hours, from a different vantage point.',
            },
          ].map((example) => (
            <div class="example-card">
              <div class="example-origin">{example.origin}</div>
              <div class="example-arrow">→</div>
              <div class="example-became">{example.became}</div>
              <p class="example-desc">{example.desc}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Why document them -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="t-label mb-8">Why document them?</h2>
        <div class="prose-section">
          <p>The purpose of Editorial Intelligence OS is not to describe one organisation's marketing strategy.</p>
          <p>It is to document repeatable editorial methods that can be adapted across thought leadership, customer marketing, PR, sales enablement, content strategy and knowledge management.</p>
          <p>Editorial teams generate enormous amounts of organisational knowledge. Most of it disappears — into completed projects, departed colleagues, outdated documents.</p>
          <p class="font-medium text-[var(--color-ink)]">Editorial Intelligence helps that knowledge compound instead of disappearing.</p>
          <p>The frameworks here are not complete or final. They are documented at the point where they've proven useful — stable enough to share, open enough to develop.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Evidence of reuse -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="t-label mb-3">Evidence of reuse</h2>
        <p class="t-small mb-8" style="color: var(--color-ink-tertiary)">Examples where Editorial Intelligence assets were adopted, republished or extended beyond their original context.</p>

        <div class="evidence-intro prose-section mb-10">
          <p>There are three kinds of evidence that Editorial Intelligence is working.</p>
          <p><strong style="color: var(--color-ink); font-weight: 500;">Framework evidence</strong> — research programmes and strategic models that hold up across multiple uses. Hidden Hours, AI Maturity Curve.</p>
          <p><strong style="color: var(--color-ink); font-weight: 500;">Operational evidence</strong> — experiments and workflows that work in practice. Event Intelligence, Editorial Brief Generator, AI Action Workbook.</p>
          <p><strong style="color: var(--color-ink); font-weight: 500;">Market evidence</strong> — examples where the work was adopted, republished or reused by external organisations without being commissioned to do so. That's a different signal: it suggests the ideas have value beyond their original platform.</p>
          <p>The Enterprise Nation republication is the first documented example of the third kind.</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Case study card -->
        <div class="reuse-card">
          <div class="reuse-card-header">
            <div>
              <span class="reuse-label">Case study</span>
              <h3 class="reuse-title">Enterprise Nation republication</h3>
            </div>
            <span class="reuse-tag">Market evidence</span>
          </div>

          <p class="reuse-desc">Three articles developed from the AI Maturity Curve framework were independently republished by Enterprise Nation — a leading small business platform — extending their reach to a new audience without requiring new content to be produced.</p>

          <!-- Timeline -->
          <div class="reuse-timeline">
            {[
              { step: 'Research', detail: 'Sage & AccountingWeb AI survey — 71% adoption, 7% transformation' },
              { step: 'Framework', detail: 'AI Maturity Curve — four stages, capacity gap concept' },
              { step: 'Sage publication', detail: 'Three articles developed from the framework' },
              { step: 'Enterprise Nation republication', detail: 'Independent adoption by a small business platform', highlight: true },
              { step: 'New audience', detail: 'Small business owners and advisers beyond the accounting sector' },
            ].map((item, i) => (
              <div class="timeline-step">
                <div class={`timeline-node${item.highlight ? ' timeline-node--highlight' : ''}`}></div>
                <div class="timeline-content">
                  <span class={`timeline-step-label${item.highlight ? ' timeline-step-label--highlight' : ''}`}>{item.step}</span>
                  <span class="timeline-detail">{item.detail}</span>
                </div>
                {i < 4 && <div class="timeline-line"></div>}
              </div>
            ))}
          </div>

          <!-- Articles -->
          <div class="reuse-articles">
            <p class="reuse-articles-label">Republished articles</p>
            {[
              {
                title: 'Where is your accounting or bookkeeping firm on the AI maturity curve?',
                url: 'https://www.enterprisenation.com/learn-something/ai-maturity-curve-accounting-bookkeeping-firms/',
              },
              {
                title: 'What to automate: 30-day AI wins for accounting firms',
                url: 'https://www.enterprisenation.com/learn-something/30-day-ai-wins-accounting-bookkeeping-firms/',
              },
              {
                title: 'How to try AI without breaking your business',
                url: 'https://www.enterprisenation.com/learn-something/how-to-try-ai-without-breaking-your-business/',
              },
            ].map((article) => (
              <a href={article.url} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="reuse-article-link">
                <svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none" aria-hidden="true" style="flex-shrink:0; margin-top: 0.15em">
                  <path d="M2 6h8M6 2l4 4-4 4" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
                </svg>
                {article.title}
              </a>
            ))}
          </div>

          <p class="reuse-note">External republication is one indicator that a framework has value beyond its original context. It is not the measure of success — but it is a signal worth documenting.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <!-- Organisational capability -->
      <section class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="t-label mb-8">From personal framework to organisational capability</h2>
        <div class="prose-section mb-10">
          <p>The next step is not creating more frameworks. It is embedding the strongest methods into real workflows.</p>
          <p>A framework that lives in one person's practice has limited value. The same method embedded across a team becomes a different kind of asset.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="capability-grid">
          {[
            { role: 'Thought leadership', need: 'Repeatable research-to-narrative workflows' },
            { role: 'Sales', need: 'Connected narratives that answer real objections' },
            { role: 'PR', need: 'Research stories with built-in evidence trails' },
            { role: 'Customer marketing', need: 'Consistent insight from every customer conversation' },
            { role: 'Content writers', need: 'Faster, clearer editorial briefs' },
            { role: 'Case study owners', need: 'Consistent quality and reusable proof points' },
          ].map((item) => (
            <div class="capability-row">
              <span class="capability-role">{item.role}</span>
              <span class="capability-need">{item.need}</span>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
        <div class="prose-section mt-10">
          <p>When these methods make those jobs easier, Editorial Intelligence becomes operational capability rather than a personal project.</p>
          <p>That's the direction this site is moving in.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .prose-section p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  /* Flow diagram */
  .flow-diagram {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .flow-step {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: stretch;
  }

  .flow-content {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.25rem;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    background: var(--color-surface-secondary);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
  }

  .flow-step:last-child .flow-content {
    border-bottom: none;
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 8%, var(--color-surface));
  }

  .flow-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  .flow-step:last-child .flow-label {
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .flow-desc {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .flow-arrow {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 0.2rem 0;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
  }

  /* Examples grid */
  .examples-grid {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .example-card {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr;
    grid-template-rows: auto auto;
    gap: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
    padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    align-items: center;
  }

  .example-card:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .example-origin {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  .example-arrow {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    grid-row: 1;
    grid-column: 2;
  }

  .example-became {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  .example-desc {
    grid-column: 1 / -1;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0.25rem 0 0;
  }

  /* Capability grid */
  .capability-grid {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .capability-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 10rem 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
    padding: 0.875rem 1.25rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    align-items: baseline;
  }

  .capability-row:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .capability-role {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  .capability-need {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  /* Editorial system callout */
  .system-callout {
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: var(--color-surface-secondary);
  }

  .system-callout-header {
    padding: 0.75rem 1.25rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    background: var(--color-surface);
  }

  .system-callout-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .system-callout-cols {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0;
    padding: 1.25rem;
  }

  .system-col {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }

  .system-col p {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .system-col-head {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
  }

  .system-col--to .system-col-head {
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .system-col-arrow {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    padding: 0 1.25rem;
    align-self: center;
  }

  .system-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.2rem;
  }

  .system-list li {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  .system-col--to .system-list li {
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
  }

  .system-callout-note {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.25rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Evidence of reuse */
  .reuse-card {
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: var(--color-surface-secondary);
  }

  .reuse-card-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .reuse-label {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }

  .reuse-title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .reuse-tag {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 40%, transparent);
    border-radius: 3px;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.5rem;
    white-space: nowrap;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .reuse-desc {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  /* Timeline */
  .reuse-timeline {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    padding: 1.25rem;
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-radius: 4px;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .timeline-step {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1rem 1fr;
    grid-template-rows: auto auto;
    column-gap: 0.875rem;
  }

  .timeline-node {
    width: 0.5rem;
    height: 0.5rem;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    margin-top: 0.3rem;
    grid-row: 1;
    grid-column: 1;
    justify-self: center;
  }

  .timeline-node--highlight {
    background: var(--color-accent);
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 20%, transparent);
  }

  .timeline-line {
    width: 1px;
    height: 1.25rem;
    background: var(--color-rule);
    grid-row: 2;
    grid-column: 1;
    justify-self: center;
  }

  .timeline-content {
    grid-row: 1;
    grid-column: 2;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.1rem;
    padding-bottom: 0.1rem;
  }

  .timeline-step-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  .timeline-step-label--highlight {
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .timeline-detail {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    line-height: 1.4;
    padding-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  /* Articles */
  .reuse-articles {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .reuse-articles-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .reuse-article-link {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    line-height: 1.5;
    transition: opacity 0.15s;
  }

  .reuse-article-link:hover {
    opacity: 0.75;
  }

  .reuse-note {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    padding-top: 1rem;
    margin: 0;
    font-style: italic;
  }
</style>
